MIPS-3D
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MIPS-3D
MIPS-3D is an extension to the MIPS V instruction set architecture (ISA) that added 13 new instructions for improving the performance of 3D graphics applications. The instructions improved performance by reducing the number of instructions required to implement four common 3D graphics operations: vertex transformation, clipping, transformation and lighting. For vertex transformation: ADDR For clipping: CABS BC1ANY2F BC1ANY2T BC1ANY4F BC1ANY4T For perspective division and normalization: RECIP1 RECIP2 RSQRT1 RSQRT2 Thekkath, Radhika et al. (1999) "An Architecture Extension for Efficient Geometry Processing". Hot Chips Symposium.[dead link] This computer hardware article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it. v t e
